       State Map

                    Columbia County

                                           Click a number on the map below
                                                 for launch details.

                         columbia.gif (77025 bytes)

   Up Arrow to Map   1. Lyons Ferry Marina

        Waterbody: Lake Herbert G. West
        Site Manager: Columbia Port of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Flush
     Fuel Available
     Water Available

                                Boat Launch Type:

                                  1 Loading Float
                                  1 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     70 Paved and Striped Spaces

                                Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                  23 Paved and Striped Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Othello, W on SR 26 to Washtucna; S on SR 260 7 mi; L on SR
        261; go 15 mi; R on Lyons Ferry Rd, immediate R to Marina.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a gentle to moderate grade. The concrete planks
        are in good condition and the traction is adequate. The gravel
        between the planks is beginning to erode. Lyons Ferry Marina also
        has boat moorage, boat storage, lawn areas, picnic tables, BBQ
        grills, cafe & convenience store, R.V. campsites with water and
        electric hookups, and a tent camping area. A fee is charged for the
        use of the ramp ($4.00). This site is a joint cooperative effort
        between the Corps of Engineers and the Port of Columbia County.
        However, the marina is operated by a private concessionaire.


   Up Arrow to Map   2. Tucannon Habitat Management Unit

        Waterbody: Tucannon River
        Site Manager: Corps of Engineers Walla Walla
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Portable Sani Can

                                 Boat Launch Type:

                                   1 Natural Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     20 Gravel Spaces

                                 Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                   None

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - high river levels may prevent access onto the river.

        Driving Directions:

        From Starbuck, NW on SR 261 3 mi; site on R.
        Site Description:

        The launching site is located on a moderate current section of the
        river. This site is for hand launch only. There is no access for
        trailered boats to launch here. No designated disabled parking. The
        gravel road to the launching area is rough and can become muddy
        during periods of wet weather.


   Up Arrow to Map   3. Texas Rapids Recreation Area

        Waterbody: Lake Herbert G. West
        Site Manager: Corps of Engineers Walla Walla
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Flush
     Restroom - Portable Sani Can
     Water Available

                                 Boat Launch Type:

                                   1 Concrete Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     10 Gravel Spaces

                                 Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                   30 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Starbuck, W on SR 261 1 mi; R on Little Goose Dam Rd; go 5 mi;
        L to recreation area.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate grade and adequate traction. A jetty
        protects the ramp from waves. An abrupt edge has developed on the
        left side of the ramp. Texas Rapids Recreation Area also provides a
        small lawn area, covered picnic tables, fire rings, a boat tie-up
        area, and fishing access.


   Up Arrow to Map   4. Little Goose Landing

        Waterbody: Lake Herbert G. West
        Site Manager: Corps of Engineers Walla Walla
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Loading Float
                            1 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            23 Paved and Striped Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Starbuck, W on SR 261 1 mi; R on Little Goose Dam Rd 10 mi to
        Little Goose Dam; at S end of dam, continue E 1.2 mi end of Rd.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp at Little Goose Landing has a moderate grade and
        adequate traction. A few of the concrete planks are chipped and the
        ramp base material is beginning to wash away. The boat ramp is
        somewhat protected by its location in a small cove. No designated
        disabled parking. Little Goose Landing also has a small lawn area,
        picnic tables, fire rings, fishing & hunting access, and a garbage
        bag dispenser.



